Name: Ingredient
Description: A compound or moiety that gives the drug its distinctive clinical properties. Ingredients generally use the United States Adopted Name (USAN).

Name: Precise Ingredient
Description: A specified form of the ingredient that may or may not be clinically active. Most precise ingredients are salt or isomer forms.

Name: Multiple Ingredients
Description: Two or more ingredients appearing together in a single drug preparation, created from SCDF. In rare cases when IN/PIN or PIN/PIN combinations of the same base ingredient exist, created from SCD.

Name: Semantic Clinical Drug Component
Description: Ingredient + Strength

Name: Semantic Clinical Drug Form
Description: Ingredient + Dose Form

Name: Semantic Clinical Dose Form Group
Description: Ingredient + Dose Form Group

Name: Semantic Clinical Drug
Description: Ingredient + Strength + Dose Form

Name: Generic Pack
Description: {# (Ingredient + Strength + Dose Form) / # (Ingredient + Strength + Dose Form)} Pack
Example: {11 (varenicline 0.5 MG Oral Tablet) / 42 (varenicline 1 MG Oral Tablet) } Pack

Name: Brand Name
Description: A proprietary name for a family of products containing a specific active ingredient.

Name: Semantic Branded Drug Component
Description: Ingredient + Strength + Brand Name

Name: Semantic Branded Drug Form
Description: Ingredient + Dose Form + Brand Name

Name: Semantic Branded Dose Form Group
Description: Brand Name + Dose Form Group

Name: Semantic Branded Drug
Description: Ingredient + Strength + Dose Form + Brand Name

Name: Brand Name Pack
Description: {# (Ingredient Strength Dose Form) / # (Ingredient Strength Dose Form)} Pack [Brand Name]
Example: {12 (Ethinyl Estradiol 0.035 MG / Norethindrone 0.5 MG Oral Tablet) / 9 (Ethinyl Estradiol 0.035 MG / Norethindrone 1 MG Oral Tablet) / 7 (Inert Ingredients 1 MG Oral Tablet) } Pack [Leena 28 Day]

Name: Prescribable Name
Description: Synonym of another TTY, given for clarity and for display purposes in electronic prescribing applications. Only one PSN per concept.

Name: Synonym
Description: Synonym of another TTY, given for clarity.

Name: Tall Man Lettering Synonym
Description: Tall Man Lettering synonym of another TTY, given to distinguish between commonly confused drugs.

Name: Dose Form
Description: See Appendix 2 for a full list of Dose Forms.

Name: Dose Form Entry Term
Description: Entry terms for dose forms (TTY=DF).

Name: Dose Form Group
Description: See Appendix 3 for a full list of Dose Form Groups.
